The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 August is 63,932 (7,368.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 August, there were 2,397 new confirmed cases (276.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 August, there were 2,575 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 7% (178 fewer cases).
